{
 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "# Comparison of interpolation methods\n",
    "We compare the results of our interpolation method versus reproject to verify the results."
   ],
   "id": "cf9e6f3c3cb0b117"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:04.595514Z",
     "start_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:02.122943Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "from astropy.io import fits\n",
    "from astropy.wcs import WCS\n",
    "import time\n",
    "from dfreproject import calculate_reprojection\n",
    "from reproject import reproject_interp\n",
    "from demo.create_test_data import create_test_fits_tiny\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "import cmcrameri.cm as cmc\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ],
   "id": "e95959819f1dfec1",
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": 2
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Create data\n",
    "We are going to create a sample dataset of three Gaussian sources with a subpixel (0.2 pixel) shift with the relevant WCS information."
   ],
   "id": "d1529824ea9d53e9"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:04.615225Z",
     "start_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:04.602259Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "source_file, target_file = create_test_fits_tiny()\n",
    "source_hdu = fits.open(source_file)[0]\n",
    "target_hdu = fits.open(target_file)[0]"
   ],
   "id": "cf9fee248fa3e643",
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": 3
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Run Reprojection\n",
    "We are now going to run reprojection using our `dfreproject` package and the standard `reproject` package for comparison. Let's compare the results using the three types of interpolation we have: 'nearest-neighbor', 'bilinear', and 'bicubic'. Since the images are very small, the timing advantage isn't seen in our implementation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Nearest Neighbor"
   ],
   "id": "abf3634de02cf2b3"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:06.256560Z",
     "start_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:05.709494Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "reprojected_source_torch = calculate_reprojection(source_hdu, WCS(target_hdu.header), shape_out=target_hdu.data.shape, order=\"nearest\")\n",
    "print(f\"total time: {time.time()-start}\")"
   ],
   "id": "562cf4f9a6d0bb63",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "total time: 0.5434434413909912\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 4
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:06.888707Z",
     "start_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:06.857792Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "start = time.time()\n",
    "reprojected_source_reproj = reproject_interp(source_hdu, target_hdu.header,order='nearest-neighbor')[0]\n",
    "#reprojected_source_reproj = reproject_interp(target_hdu, source_hdu.header,order='bicubic')[0]\n",
    "print(f\"total time: {time.time()-start}\")"
   ],
   "id": "217fd46098b92fe6",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "total time: 0.026688098907470703\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 5
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:36.330431Z",
     "start_time": "2025-04-14T13:57:35.986961Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(12,6))\n",
    "axs[0].imshow(source_hdu.data, origin='lower', cmap=cmc.lipari)\n",
    "axs[0].set_title('Source')\n",
    "\n",
    "im1 = axs[1].imshow(reprojected_source_torch, origin='lower', cmap=cmc.lipari)\n",
    "axs[1].set_title(\"dfreproject\")\n",
    "\n",
    "im2 = axs[2].imshow(reprojected_source_reproj, origin='lower', cmap=cmc.lipari)\n",
    "axs[2].set_title(\"reproject\")\n",
    "\n",
    "diff_result = 100*(reprojected_source_torch.astype(np.float32)- reprojected_source_reproj.astype(np.float32))/reprojected_source_reproj.astype(np.float32)\n",
    "im3 = axs[3].imshow(diff_result, origin='lower', cmap=cmc.managua, vmin=-10, vmax=10)\n",
    "axs[3].set_title(\"Relative Error in %\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cbar_ax = fig.add_axes([0.92, 0.325, 0.02, 0.34])  # [left, bottom, width, height]\n",
    "fig.colorbar(im3, cax=cbar_ax)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "fca10d1410e9d867",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 5 Axes>"
      ],
      "image/png": ""
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 8
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "As we can see the results are extremely similar. The differences are due to how the normalization is handled in our implementation versus reproject_interp.",
   "id": "8b50398968bf1abe"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "### Bilinear",
   "id": "725542ac0b4d7049"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2025-04-14T13:59:29.048936Z",
     "start_time": "2025-04-14T13:59:28.653807Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [

    "\n",
    "im2 = axs[2].imshow(reprojected_source_reproj, origin='lower', cmap=cmc.lipari)\n",
    "axs[2].set_title(\"reproject\")\n",
    "\n",
    "diff_result = 100*(reprojected_source_torch.astype(np.float32)- reprojected_source_reproj.astype(np.float32))/reprojected_source_reproj.astype(np.float32)\n",
    "im3 = axs[3].imshow(diff_result, origin='lower', cmap=cmc.managua, vmin=-10, vmax=10)\n",
    "axs[3].set_title(\"Relative Error in %\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cbar_ax = fig.add_axes([0.92, 0.325, 0.02, 0.34])  # [left, bottom, width, height]\n",
    "fig.colorbar(im3, cax=cbar_ax)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "id": "5ac5273c7c90c46",

    {

  },
